Anonymous Tue 20 Jun 2023 22:36:16 No.57423220 Report

>>57418734
The isothiocyanates that give mustard its flavor are toxic to carnivores generally. They irritate the whole gastrointestinal tract and cause diarrhea and vomiting, sometimes to a life-threatening extent. Cabbage and its relatives contain a little too, but much less. It's why fresh cut cabbage can have a bit of a peppery smell.

Grapes and anything made from them, and this includes raisins, wine, and brandy, are also really toxic to most mammals other than primates. I have read articles suggesting they metabolize the tartaric acid differently, resulting in systemic poisoning that can cause liver and kidney failure a couple of weeks after eating them.

Chocolate is also really, really poisonous to carnivores. The caffeine and theobromine are, for them, powerful and nasty central nervous stimulants that can cause seizures, unconsciousness, and heart failure. Sort of like strychnine.

There's an artificial sweetener called xylitol--not common in the US, but more common in Australia and New Zealand--that's also really poisonous to carnivores.

In my worldbuildan I find this sort of thing sufficiently inconvenient that I edit it out and just say that anthros are not at grave risk from dying from a hundred things in the typical meal we eat. At the very least I would dial it back to make it something that can be played for comedy rather than tragedy.
